"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776949","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>I refer you to the answers previously given to the Members for Oldham West and Royton and Linlithgow and East Falkirk, PQ1118 answered on 3<sup>rd</sup> July 2017. There are no plans to introduce automatic registration, as it contradicts the principles underpinning Individual Electoral Registration. Making an application to register to vote is the right of individuals and can be done easily online, in as little as three minutes, as well as using the traditional paper form, if people prefer. The 2017 UK parliamentary general election was fought on the largest ever register, according to initial estimates.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","109371 ; 109373","2017-10-30T15:41:01.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776949/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776949/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776949/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-24","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what discussions his Department has had with other Government Departments on the potential use of automatic voter registration.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","109372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776950","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>I refer you to the answers previously given to the Members for Oldham West and Royton and Linlithgow and East Falkirk, PQ1118 answered on 3<sup>rd</sup> July 2017. There are no plans to introduce automatic registration, as it contradicts the principles underpinning Individual Electoral Registration. Making an application to register to vote is the right of individuals and can be done easily online, in as little as three minutes, as well as using the traditional paper form, if people prefer. The 2017 UK parliamentary general election was fought on the largest ever register, according to initial estimates.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","109371 ; 109372","2017-10-30T15:41:01.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776950/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776950/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776950/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-24","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the potential benefits to the electoral system of automatic voter registration for elections in the UK.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","109373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776951","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-14","<p>The four Active Cyber Defence services are described in the National Cyber Security Centre’s Annual Review, published on 3 October 2017. They include working in partnership with industry to implement a series of measures, such as a protective DNS service for public sector to prevent unwitting exposure to known malware and phishing sites. Furthermore, the government will deploy email authenticity measures on government domains to help prevent phishing activity that relies on ‘spoofing’, and encourage industry to do likewise. We will scale up and enhance disruption activities that we already undertake for cyber crime and we have launched a service to help public sector bodies find simple vulnerabilities in their websites.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-11-14T11:35:33.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776951/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776951/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776951/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-24","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 23 October 2017 to Question 7512, on cybercrime, what the four services referred to in that Answer are.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","109429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776952","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-31","<p>Until exit negotiations are concluded, the UK remains a full member of the European Union and all the rights and obligations of EU membership remain in force.</p><p> </p><p>The UK duty regime complies with EU Directives on rates and structures of alcohol excise duty. The European Commission is currently undertaking a review of the Alcohol Structures Directive and we expect this to conclude in due course.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-10-31T14:41:42.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776952/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776952/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776952/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-24","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will review the progressive beer duty regime to ensure that the excise duty system supports growth in British beer exports.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","109467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776953","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Treasury engages with a wide variety of organisations to understand industry developments, including the beer and pub industry and public health groups. This government is aware of concerns about Small Brewers Relief, it has invited views on how it can be reformed in a way that the whole sector could support. All taxes are kept under review at fiscal events, and we will consider these issues carefully as part of the Autumn Budget process.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","109469","2017-10-31T14:37:41.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776953/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776953/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776953/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-24","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will review the operation of the Small Brewers Relief scheme to remove barriers to growth for the UK's small and medium-sized brewers.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","109468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776954","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-31","<p>The Treasury engages with a wide variety of organisations to understand industry developments, including the beer and pub industry and public health groups. This government is aware of concerns about Small Brewers Relief, it has invited views on how it can be reformed in a way that the whole sector could support. All taxes are kept under review at fiscal events, and we will consider these issues carefully as part of the Autumn Budget process.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","109468","2017-10-31T14:37:41.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776954/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776954/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776954/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-24","Beer: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has considered the report from Europe Economics commissioned by the Small Brewer Duty Reform Coalition; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","109469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776955","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-30","<p>My Written Ministerial Statement of 12 October set out the UK Government’s approach to preparations for EU Exit. Where additional funding is provided to UK Government departments to prepare for EU Exit, the Scottish Government will receive additional funding through the Barnett system.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-10-30T13:55:28.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776955/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776955/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776955/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-24","Public Expenditure: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what additional funds he plans to allocate to the Scottish Government to prepare for when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Stewart Hosie","Dundee East","Stewart Hosie","109356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776956","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-31","<p>According to the Metropolitan Police, a Hotpoint fridge freezer has been identified as the initial source of the Grenfell Tower fire. Advice for members of the public who are concerned about risk from their fridge freezer is available on the Government’s Product Recall website:</p><p><a href="https://productrecall.campaign.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://productrecall.campaign.gov.uk</a></p><p>The Grenfell Tower Inquiry, set up by the Prime Minister, is examining the circumstances leading up to and surrounding the fire at Grenfell Tower on 14 June 2017. Sir Martin Moore Bick, the Chairman of the independent inquiry, hopes to provide the Prime Minister with a first report by early April next year. This report will include the development of the fire; where and how it started, how it spread and the chain of events before it was extinguished.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-10-31T15:35:03.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776956/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776956/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776956/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776956/answer/previousversion/18708","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-24","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the specific cause of the fire at Grenfell Tower has been identified; and what that cause was.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","109354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776957","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Government has no plans to introduce mandatory testing for portable appliances in residential properties.</p><p>The Electrical Equipment (Safety) Regulations 2016 require suppliers of electrical equipment to supply only safe products.</p><p>In addition, the legislation requires manufacturers of electrical products to monitor their products on the market. Should they identify unsafe equipment, they must take immediate corrective action to make the equipment safe, withdraw it or recall it. Enforcement authorities also have powers to require a manufacturer to take corrective action, including by requiring withdrawal or recall of unsafe products.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-11-01T10:44:47.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776957/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776957/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776957/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-24","Domestic Appliances: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the timetable is for the introduction of mandatory portable appliance testing for residential properties.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","109392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776958","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Government is committed to making membership of a Client Money Protection scheme mandatory for letting and managing agents to ensure that tenants and landlords get the financial protection they want and deserve. A consultation seeking views on the detail of implementation was launched on 1 November ahead of bringing legislation forward.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-01T16:21:52.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776958/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776958/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776958/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-24","Client Money Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans for the provisions of the Housing and Planning Act 2016 relating to client money protection to come into force.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","109393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776959","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-30","<p>We have no specific plans to analyse the potential effect of videos demonstrating skin bleaching.</p><p> </p><p>However, as part of the work on the Digital Charter, we are considering a range of options to counter internet harms. This includes an Internet Safety Strategy, published on 11 October, which considers the responsibilities of companies to their users, the use of technical solutions to prevent online harms and government's role in supporting users.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-10-30T12:03:00.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776959/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776959/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776959/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-24","Cosmetics: Video Recordings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 18 September 2017 to Question 9919, if her Department will make an analysis of the harm done by skin bleaching videos and options for regulation.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","109399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776960","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Government is continuing to assess the impact of leaving the EU on charities and social enterprises, which includes access to future funding. Officials in my department are working with colleagues across government to inform plans for future funds, which includes the UK Shared Prosperity Fund.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","109353","2017-10-30T11:57:21.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776960/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776960/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776960/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-24","Social Enterprises: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she has taken to ensure that charities and social enterprises that receive funding from the EU can receive a similar level of funding after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","109349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776961","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-30","<p>The London Legacy Development Corporation, the body responsible for the regeneration of Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park and surrounding area following the London 2012 Games, owns the assets on the Park and is responsible for their disposal.</p><p>To date the Legacy Corporation has entered into development agreements for three housing neighbourhoods on the Park - Chobham Manor, East Wick and Sweetwater - for which it has so far received £38 million in deposits and land receipts.</p><p>In addition the Olympic Park Legacy Company, the Legacy Corporation's predecessor, sold land at Sugar House Lane near to the Park for £19.5m in 2011.</p><p>Total revenue to date is, therefore, £57.5 million.</p><p>Future receipts will be generated as the housing sites under construction are built out and development agreements are entered into for additional housing sites at Stratford Waterfront, Pudding Mill and Rick Roberts Way.</p><p>The Legacy Corporation has also entered into a long-term lease for the new business district being developed on the site of the former Press and Broadcast Centre, Here East, and long-term leases will be let to the institutions involved in the planned culture and education district on south of the Park.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-30T12:00:43.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776961/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776961/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776961/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-24","Olympic Games 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of the assets at the Olympic Park have been sold; what revenue those sales have yielded; and what further such sales of assets are planned.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","109351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776962","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Government is continuing to assess the impact of leaving the EU on charities and social enterprises, which includes access to future funding. Officials in my department are working with colleagues across government to inform plans for future funds, which includes the UK Shared Prosperity Fund.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","109349","2017-10-30T11:57:20.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776962/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776962/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776962/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-24","Social Enterprises: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she has taken to ensure that charities and social enterprises can bid for funding from the proposed UK Shared Prosperity Fund.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","109353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776963","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>A team of seven UK Armed Forces personnel have been providing training and mentoring to African Parks rangers since August in Liwonde National Park, Malawi.</p><p>In November a short term training team of 11 UK Armed Forces personnel will travel to Gabon, to train up to 60 rangers from the Agence Nationale des Parcs Nationaux in counter-poaching patrolling skills.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-31T16:12:48.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776963/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776963/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776963/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","Poaching","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what training and assistance the UK armed forces are providing to support anti-poaching patrols in other countries.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776964","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>As at 1 September 2017, the Army Reserve - Future Reserves 2020* total strength was 30,280. This is an increase of 1,000 personnel since 1 September 2016.</p><p>* Future Reserves 2020 includes volunteer reserves who are mobilised, high readiness reserves and those volunteer reserves serving on Full Time Reserve Service and Additional Duties Commitment. Sponsored reserves, who provide a more cost effective solution than volunteer reserves, are also included.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-30T16:14:16.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776964/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776964/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776964/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","Army Reserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress his Department has made on increasing the size of the Army Reserve to 30,000 personnel.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776965","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>We want to help all schools to deliver high-quality Relationships Education, Relationships and Sex Education (RSE) and Personal, Social, Health and Economic (PSHE) Education so that all young people are equipped to have healthy and respectful relationships, and leave school with the knowledge to prepare them for adult life.</p><p>The Department remains fully committed to conducting thorough and wide-ranging engagement with stakeholders, which will help us to reach evidence-based decisions on the content of the regulations and statutory guidance, as well as on the status of PSHE. We will set out shortly more details about the engagement process, the timetable and the work to consider age-appropriate subject content. We will consult on draft regulations and guidance and the regulations will then be laid in the House allowing for a full and considered debate. We are working towards schools teaching the new subjects from September 2019.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-10-30T17:01:02.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776965/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776965/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776965/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Sex and Relationship Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Written Statement of 1 March 2017, Sex and Relationships Education, HCWS 509, and pursuant to the Answer of 11 July 2017 to Question 2526, what the (a) timetable and (b) planned commencement date is for the consultation on the provision of relationships education.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","109340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776966","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>Academy trusts operate under a strict system of oversight and accountability. Academy trusts must adhere to their funding agreement and to the Academies Financial Handbook. They are also subject to company and charities law. All academy trusts provide the Department with annual accounts; these accounts are subject to a system of independent audit. They are published by Trusts. As part of this process, external auditors set out whether any irregular spending has come to their attention. Following the Trust’s decision to wind-down, we have secured additional specialist capacity to provide further assurance on the Trust’s financial position.</p><p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) periodically visits multi academy trusts to assess their financial management and governance arrangements. We do not publish these routine assurance reports.</p><p>The ESFA undertook such a review of Wakefield City Academies Trust between June and September 2015 and made a follow-up visit in July 2016. At this time, we do not intend to publish the ESFA report into Wakefield City Academies Trust, as this could be obstructive to the process of ensuring all the schools are placed with new trusts.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","109404","2017-10-30T17:48:28.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776966/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776966/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776966/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Wakefield City Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when the Education Funding Agency plans to publish its report into Wakefield City Academies Trust; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776967","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) periodically visit academy trusts to assess their financial management and governance arrangements; this includes multi-academy trusts reviews. We do not routinely publish these assurance reports. Where a concern is identified, ESFA will respond proportionate to the severity of the risk, taking into account the scale and nature of the issue, and any local circumstances. Where there are significant concerns about financial management or governance in an academy trust, ESFA may visit the trust to investigate and/or issue, and publish, a Financial Notice to Improve, available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/academies-financial-notices-to-improve" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/academies-financial-notices-to-improve</a>. The trust must comply with the terms of a Financial Notice to Improve; failure to comply will be deemed a breach of the funding agreement.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","109403","2017-10-30T17:50:38.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776967/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776967/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776967/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether her Department or any of its agencies hold reports that raise concerns on the financial situation in multi-academy trusts; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109402"
