n-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776970","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The department will continue to allocate Service Pupil Premium funding to maintained schools in England that are attended by eligible pupils (those who currently have Service child status or have been recorded as Service children in the school census at any point in the last six years) for the duration of the current Spending Review period.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:56:08.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776970/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776970/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776970/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Service Pupil Premium: Plymouth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether schools in Plymouth which accept children of servicemen and servicewomen will continue to receive the service pupil premium after April 2018.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","109355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776971","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>Academy trusts operate under a strict system of oversight and accountability. The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) periodically visits multi academy trusts to assess their financial management and governance arrangements. We do not publish these routine assurance reports. The ESFA undertook a routine review of Wakefield City Academies Trust between June and September 2015 and made a follow-up visit in July 2016. At this time, we do not intend to publish the ESFA report into Wakefield City Academies Trust, as this could be obstructive to the process of ensuring all the schools are placed with new trusts.</p><p>The Department is working closely with Wakefield City Academy Trust to manage a smooth transition for its pupils. The Department’s priority is to ensure that all children receive the best possible education, by transferring the schools to trusts that will be better able to improve outcomes for pupils.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","109338","2017-10-30T17:52:27.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776971/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776971/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776971/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Wakefield City Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will place in the Library a copy of the Education Funding Agency investigation into the Wakefield City Academies Trust produced in 2016.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","109337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776972","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>Academy trusts operate under a strict system of oversight and accountability. The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) periodically visits multi academy trusts to assess their financial management and governance arrangements. We do not publish these routine assurance reports. The ESFA undertook a routine review of Wakefield City Academies Trust between June and September 2015 and made a follow-up visit in July 2016. At this time, we do not intend to publish the ESFA report into Wakefield City Academies Trust, as this could be obstructive to the process of ensuring all the schools are placed with new trusts.</p><p>The Department is working closely with Wakefield City Academy Trust to manage a smooth transition for its pupils. The Department’s priority is to ensure that all children receive the best possible education, by transferring the schools to trusts that will be better able to improve outcomes for pupils.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","109337","2017-10-30T17:52:27.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776972/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776972/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776972/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Wakefield City Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether she plans to hold an inquiry into the operation of the Wakefield City Academies Trust.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","109338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776973","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Department collected data on the household income of parents using 30 hours free childcare during the Early Implementation of the policy in eight local authorities. The independent published evaluation of early implementation summarised the income of parents that:</p><ul><li>Used 30 hours</li><li>Used more childcare than in the past because of 30 hours</li><li>Changed their employment or working hours because of using 30 hours.</li></ul><p>An independent evaluation will take place of the first two terms of national rollout of the policy. The evaluation intends to collect data from parents, including their household income.</p><p>The Department also collates some information on parent income through the annual Childcare and Early Years Survey of Parents, which provides Official Statistics on parents’ use of childcare and early years provision.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:45:49.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776973/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776973/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776973/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 23 October 2017 to Question 108171, whether her Department plans to seek information on the income of people accessing 30 hours of free childcare.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","109339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776974","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>On 11 April 2017, we announced the allocation of £100 million of capital funding to create 30-hours places for eligible children to help meet demand from hardworking parents.</p><p> </p><p>This funding was allocated to over 350 projects in 123 local councils in January 2017 and March 2017.</p><p> </p><p>We are working closely with all projects awarded funding and will publish the outcomes in due course when all projects have completed.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T17:19:14.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776974/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776974/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776974/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the announcement by her Department on 11 April 2017 on families to benefit from £55 million boost to childcare services, how many applications have been made to that fund; how much has been paid out from that fund; and how many childcare places that funding has established.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","109407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776975","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Department regularly meets with teaching unions who represent the views of their members, which include supply teachers. The last meeting my department held to specifically discuss supply teacher working practices was in October 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is aware of concerns about insecure working practices for supply teachers, in particular relating to practices of some supply teacher agencies. The Department is in the planning phase of a new commercial framework for schools that use supply agencies. The Department will discuss these proposals with the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, particularly in relation to the Taylor Review of modern working practices.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","109278","2017-10-30T17:09:40.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776975/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776975/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776975/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Supply Teachers: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Taylor Review of modern working practices, published in July 2017, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy to improve the working practices in the supply teaching profession.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Theresa Villiers","109408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776976","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>Defra’s science, evidence and analysis budget is allocated each year in support of policy objectives, in the areas of environment, food, farming and animal and plant health. The figures below are for all policy areas, and include surveillance, monitoring and analysis as well as research. Figures are for core Defra, and do not include the Department's Non Departmental Public Bodies, Arm’s Length Bodies, or Executive Agencies. Following the 2015 Spending Review, allocations are divided between revenue, capital, and Official Development Assistance (ODA) research.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Programme Evidence</p></td><td><p>Capital Research and Development</p></td><td><p><strong>Sub-total: Non-ODA evidence budget</strong></p></td><td><p>ODA</p></td><td><p><strong>Total: Science, Evidence &amp; Analysis budget</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>163.27</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p><strong>163.27</strong></p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p><strong>163.27</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>142.13</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p><strong>142.13</strong></p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p><strong>142.13</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>119.45</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p><strong>119.45</strong></p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td><td><p><strong>119.45</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>24.54</p></td><td><p>20.91</p></td><td><p><strong>45.45</strong></p></td><td><p>4.10</p></td><td><p><strong>49.55</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>25.36</p></td><td><p>18.90</p></td><td><p><strong>44.26</strong></p></td><td><p>4.13</p></td><td><p><strong>48.39</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>(Figures are in £million)</p><p> </p><p>The figures for 2016/17 and 2017/18 are not comparable with those for earlier years due to reallocation of budgets from core Defra to Defra's Laboratory Agencies, the Animal and Plant Health Agency (APHA), Centre for Environment, Fisheries and Aquaculture Science (Cefas), Veterinary Medicines Directorate (VMD), and the Environment Agency. <strong><br> </strong></p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-11-06T12:09:30.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776976/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776976/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776976/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Environment: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much his Department allocated to scientific research in the UK on the environment in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776977","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-06","<p>The UK is one of 127 member governments of the Intergovernmental Science-Policy Platform for Biodiversity and Ecosystem Services. This is currently undertaking the most comprehensive ever assessment of changing global ecosystems and their importance to human societies.</p><p> </p><p>In March 2018, members of the Platform will meet to adopt four Regional Assessments of Biodiversity and Ecosystem Services, which together cover the entire planet except Antarctica and the open oceans.</p><p> </p><p>The UK government has supported this Platform since its inception and will continue to publicise its reports where they are relevant and of interest to the public.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-11-06T12:04:08.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776977/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776977/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776977/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Environment: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department takes to update the public on new and scientific discoveries about challenges to ecosystems across the world.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776978","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-01","<p>Defra, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and other Government Departments work in partnership to deliver global leadership on ocean conservation. Our commitment to ocean conservation was most recently demonstrated at the Our Ocean Conference in Malta on 5-6 October and the UN Oceans Conference in June. A list of the commitments made by the United Kingdom at the Malta Conference is available at: <a href="https://ourocean2017.org/sites/default/files/ooc-2017-list-of-commitments_en.pdf" target="_blank">https://ourocean2017.org/sites/default/files/ooc-2017-list-of-commitments_en.pdf</a> and the UN Ocean Conference at <a href="https://oceanconference.un.org/commitments/" target="_blank">https://oceanconference.un.org/commitments/</a></p><p> </p><p>Looking forward, we will use the Commonwealth Summit in 2018 to ensure that ocean issues remain central to future work within the Commonwealth and support the initiative of the Commonwealth Secretary General to develop a “blue charter” for the Commonwealth. We will also continue to push for a new international agreement under the UN for the conservation and sustainable use of marine biodiversity in areas beyond national jurisdiction, which will deliver effective protected areas for the world’s oceans.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-11-01T18:13:02.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776978/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776978/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776978/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Marine Environment: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Foreign Secretary on the role of the UK in demonstrating global leadership on ocean conservation.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776979","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-01","<p>Defra works closely with colleagues in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office on issues relating to the protection of the Antarctic including the designation of marine protected areas (MPAs). The UK led the proposal to establish an MPA around the South Orkney Islands Southern Shelf, agreed in 2009, through the Convention for the Conservation of Antarctic Marine Living Resources and strongly supported the designation of the Ross Sea Region MPA. The UK supports proposals for MPAs in the Weddell Sea, East Antarctic and the Antarctic Peninsula regions of the Southern Ocean.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-11-01T12:07:00.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776979/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776979/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776979/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Marine Environment: Antarctic","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to further the roll-out of marine sanctuaries in the Antarctic.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776980","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>​We recognise the extraordinary contribution Parliamentarians can make to the Commonwealth's rejuvenation, both by sharing their wealth of expertise and knowledge and by contributing to activities that celebrate the Commonwealth across the UK in the run up to and during the week of the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting.</p><p>Lord Ahmad, Minister for the Commonwealth, is in regular contact with parliamentarians from both Houses, engaging with the All Party Parliamentary Group, through Commonwealth Organisations such as the Commonwealth Parliamentary Association UK and by meeting many Parliamentarians individually to set out our plans. Lord Ahmad plans to write to Parliamentarians in both Houses shortly to outline further details regarding the summit.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-30T16:23:17.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776980/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776980/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776980/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to communicate with hon. Members and Members of the House of Lords plans for the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting 2018.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776981","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-01","<p>As part of the Foreign Office's efforts to imporve the UK's international relations, we work with a number of private organisations. To identify every private organisation we work with from within our 18,000 suppliers would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-11-01T17:30:04.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776981/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776981/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776981/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","International Relations: Private Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much his Department has provided to private organisations that work to improve the UK's international relations in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776982","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-01","<p>We maintain a close dialogue with the Intergovernmental Authority on Development IGAD) and key regional actors, including Uganda and Kenya. Through sustained ministerial and senior official engagement, we encourage their continued and vital role in taking forward the Revitalisation Forum. We welcome the IGAD communiqué of 17 October, which noted positive and constructive progress made in initial talks with all significant parties to the conflict</p><p>The Forum is a critical opportunity for the restoration of peace in South Sudan. Only dialogue that involves a broad range of actors can bring a lasting resolution. We continue to encourage the Government of South Sudan and the opposition to engage meaningfully.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-11-01T14:28:23.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776982/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776982/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776982/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","South Sudan: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to encourage the Governments of Uganda and Kenya to participate in the Intergovernmental Authority on Development-led High-Level Revitalisation Forum.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","109389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776983","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Prime Minister discussed the situation in Catalonia with the Spanish Prime Minister Mariano Rajoy on 17 October and expressed the UK's support for the rule of law and respect for the Spanish constitution. This followed a meeting between myself and the Spanish Ambassador Carlos Bastarreche on 11 October, after which I released a public statement.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-10-30T17:41:00.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776983/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776983/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776983/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Catalonia: Civil Disorder","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his Spanish counterpart on the violence that occurred during the Catalan independence referendum; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","109475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776984","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Overseas Territories Joint Ministerial Council will be held on 28 – 29 November. Items currently on the agenda for discussion include: disaster relief and recovery; environment and climate change resilience; sustainable economic development; child safeguarding; tax transparency and beneficial ownership; and implications for the Overseas Territories of EU Exit.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-10-30T17:43:13.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776984/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776984/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776984/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Overseas Territories Joint Ministerial Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when the Overseas Territories Joint Ministerial Council will be held in 2017; and what the agenda is for that meeting.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","109343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776985","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>I have not raised the International Labour Organization’s Domestic Workers Convention, 2011 (No. 189). The UK has not seen the need to ratify this Convention, given the effective provisions in our domestic law, but supports the Convention’s principles. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not have primary policy responsibility for this Convention.</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td></tr></tbody></table>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-10-30T15:23:44.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776985/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776985/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776985/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Domestic Service: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterparts in other countries on ratification of the International Labour Organisation Convention on Domestic Workers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","109367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776986","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>​I speak regularly to US Secretary of State Rex Tillerson to discuss a range of issues, including nuclear issues, as part of our strong bilateral cooperation on security and defence policy. As I set out in my Chatham House Conference speech on 23 October, the Government remains determined to continue to work with partners across the international community to address threats to our security, to prevent proliferation and where possible to make progress on multilateral nuclear disarmament.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-10-30T15:25:44.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776986/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776986/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776986/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","USA: Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has made with his US counterpart on that Government's current Nuclear Posture Review.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","109368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776987","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>​The UK fully supports the territorial integrity of Nigeria and President Buhari's commitment to work for a secure and prosperous Nigeria. We are committed to working with Nigeria to help tackle threats to national security and to address the underlying causes of instability which exist within Nigeria.</p><p>We echo President Buhari's calls for calm and reconciliation between the ethnic groups and communities that make up and contribute to the strength and diversity of the Federal Republic of Nigeria.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-10-30T15:27:40.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776987/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776987/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776987/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Nigeria: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on self-determination for the Biafran people in the Eastern Region of Nigeria.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","109413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776988","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>The UK strongly supports UN Security Council Resolution 1540, including by helping States to implement their obligations under the resolution to take effective measures to prevent the proliferation of nuclear, chemical and biological weapons and their means of delivery. We are assisting several African countries to report on their implementation of the resolution, and support lobbying by the EU and G7 to encourage more States to submit such reports. We support work by the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) to promote chemical safety and security, and work bilaterally, with the OPCW and in other fora to address the safety and security of toxic industrial chemicals, including through the OPCW’s Programme for Africa. We worked with partners to secure an OPCW Decision on 16 October encouraging States to take measures to combat the threat of chemical terrorism. We are assisting States to adopt legislation and regulations to implement their obligations under the Biological and Toxin Weapons Convention, and have supported work to promote biological security education globally. Through the Global Initiative to Combat Nuclear Terrorism we provide advice on how to implement measures to address the threat of nuclear terrorism. And through the Global Threat Reduction Programme we support substantial international efforts to secure vulnerable nuclear and radiological materials.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-10-30T15:30:18.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776988/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776988/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776988/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Weapons of Mass Destruction: Proliferation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to help facilitate implementation by UN member states of their obligations under UN Security Council Resolution 1540.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","109436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776989","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>The UK strongly supports the work of the Committee established pursuant to UN Security Council Resolution 1540, and is a vice-Chair of the Committee. We worked particularly closely with Spain, Chair of the Committee in 2016, on the five-yearly Comprehensive Review of Implementation of the Resolution. The review concluded in December 2016 that significant progress had been made in addressing the risk of proliferation of weapons of mass destruction to non-state actors, and proposed a number of measures to improve implementation further, partly as a result of our work. These included proposals to address new and emerging challenges from the evolving terrorist threat and advances in science and technology; to improve the process to match requests for technical assistance with offers of assistance; to strengthen cooperation and outreach to industry and civil society; and to strengthen the UN structures which support the resolution’s implementation. UN Security Council Resolution 2325, adopted on 15 December 2016, endorsed the review and its proposals. We are now working with Bolivia, Chair of the Committee in 2017, and other Committee members to implement the review.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-10-30T15:33:09.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776989/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776989/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776989/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Weapons of Mass Destruction: Proliferation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to support the work of the committee established pursuant to UN Security Resolution 1540.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","109437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776990","Department of Health","false","2017-11-01","<p>NHS England has made £1 million available to the NHS North Region to support the mental health care and treatment required for people affected by the Manchester Arena incident and to inform the response for future incidents.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-11-01T12:37:49.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776990/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776990/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776990/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what additional resources have been allocated to child and adolescent mental health services in Lancashire, outside the Greater Manchester region, since the Manchester area attack of 22 May 2017.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","109318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776991","Department of Health","false","2017-11-01","<p>Issues around the sexual and reproductive health workforce are being considered as part of work being taken forward by Health Education England’s Sexual Health Workforce Task and Finish Group.</p><p> </p><p>The delivery of open access sexual health services is mandated for all local authorities. Sexual and Reproductive Health Profiles have been developed by Public Health England (PHE) to support local authorities, public health leads and other interested parties to monitor the sexual and reproductive health of their population and the contribution of local public health related systems. The Department closely monitors the range of indicators and outcomes at national level.</p><p> </p><p>In 2016, PHE undertook a survey of local authorities, NHS England and clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) to highlight areas of challenge within sexual health commissioning. The survey findings form the basis of an action plan published in August 2017 within the PHE report, ‘Sexual Health, Reproductive Health and HIV: A Review of Commissioning’ report. As part of the action plan, PHE will take forward a range of activities aimed at strengthening commissioning. These actions include providing evidence and data to commissioners to support commissioning, and the monitoring of outcomes, and the building of capacity and capability in sexual and reproductive health commissioning.</p><p> </p><p>The Department's publication, ‘A Framework for Sexual Health Improvement in England’, is kept under review. There are no plans to update it at this time.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","109394 ; 109418","2017-11-01T11:45:18.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776991/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776991/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776991/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-24","Contraceptives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that GPs and nurses are able to access training to gain and maintain qualifications to fit long-acting reversible contraception.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","109330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776992","Department of Health","false","2017-10-30","<p>The information is not held in the format requested. Data on waiting times for children referred to mental health support services is not held. Data on the count of people under 18, who have a referral recorded that started on or after 1 January 2016 is reported by NHS Digital and can be viewed via the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsreports" target="_blank">http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsreports</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-10-30T16:38:21.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776992/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776992/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776992/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-24","Mental Health Services: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of children waiting for mental health support services in (a) Hounslow, (b) London and (c) England.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","109432"
