"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775969","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-03","<p>The Conservative manifesto stated Government would introduce a Cultural Development Fund to use cultural investment to turn around communities, and we will set out further details in due course.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2017-11-03T11:06:10.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775969/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775969/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775969/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-23","Culture: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what progress they have made towards the introduction of a new cultural development fund; how that fund will support the Industrial Strategy's commitment to invest in the creative industries; and what consultation will take place with local government about its development as one of the largest public funders of cultural investment.","false","Biography information for Lord Porter of Spalding",,"Lord Porter of Spalding","HL2377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775970","Department of Health","false","2017-11-02","<p>NHS England’s consultation on draft guidance for clinical commissioning groups on a range of items that should not routinely be prescribed in primary care ended on 21 October. The draft guidance seeks to ensure that the National Health Service is able to secure best value from its use of medicines and therefore focuses on areas of prescribing that have been found to be unsafe, ineffective or where there are more cost effective alternatives.</p><p> </p><p>We would not want to pre-empt any outcome following NHS England’s careful analysis of the responses it has received.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-11-02T14:49:44.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775970/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775970/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775970/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-23","Cancer: Analgesics","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether one possible outcome of NHS England’s consultation, Items which should not be routinely prescribed in primary care: consultation on guidance for CCGs, may be a limit imposed on the pain management treatments prescribed within NICE guidelines for cancer patients.","false","Biography information for Lord Porter of Spalding",,"Lord Porter of Spalding","HL2378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775971","Department of Health","false","2017-11-02","<p>NHS England will keep the run rates for each Operational Delivery Network (ODN) under review, as in 2016/17, taking into account available data on estimated need and performance across the Networks.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has a Commissioning for Quality and Innovation scheme in place for hepatitis C virus, which provides a substantial opportunity for hospitals to earn additional income for success, rather than any financial penalties. All hospitals who deliver between 90% and 100% of the planned rates of expansion receive the additional payment. In 2016/17, no ODN exceeded their run rate.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-11-02T14:59:03.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775971/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775971/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775971/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-23","Hepatitis: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they intend to review run rates for Operational Delivery Networks providing treatment for hepatitis C, in the light of current variations in the level of demand in relation to capacity.","false","Biography information for Baroness Randerson",,"Baroness Randerson","HL2379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775972","Department of Health","false","2017-11-02","<p>NHS England will keep the run rates for each Operational Delivery Network (ODN) under review, as in 2016/17, taking into account available data on estimated need and performance across the Networks.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has a Commissioning for Quality and Innovation scheme in place for hepatitis C virus, which provides a substantial opportunity for hospitals to earn additional income for success, rather than any financial penalties. All hospitals who deliver between 90% and 100% of the planned rates of expansion receive the additional payment. In 2016/17, no ODN exceeded their run rate.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-11-02T16:27:03.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775972/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775972/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775972/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-23","Hepatitis: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether any financial penalties have been applied to those Operational Delivery Networks which have exceeded their run rates for the treatment of hepatitis C.","false","Biography information for Baroness Randerson",,"Baroness Randerson","HL2380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775973","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-06","<p>It is a matter for airport operators, the companies that provide operational ground support at airports, and the specialist vehicle manufacturers to work together to determine how best to introduce ultra low emission vehicles into their airport based vehicle fleets.</p><p> </p><p>Airports operators are able to take advantage of the Office for Low Emission Vehicle’s Plug in Car Grant which offers up to £4,500 off the cost of an eligible vehicle, the Plug in Van Grant which offers a grant of up to £8,000, and which has been extended to up to £20,000 for the first 200 of the largest vehicles and the Work Place Charging Scheme which offers £300 for each of up to twenty sockets for recharging vehicles.</p><p> </p><p>Gatwick has signed up to the Go Ultra Low Companies initiative with participating companies committing to 5% of their fleet being electric vehicles by 2020. Heathrow is one of the Climate Group’s EV100 and as part of this initiative is implementing comprehensive plans to increase transition to ultra low emission airport mobility.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Sugg",,"2017-11-06T16:52:01.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775973/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775973/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775973/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-23","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they plan to provide financial support, through the Office for Low Emission Vehicles, to encourage the development of zero emission or ultra low emission specialist vehicles, such as those used for ground operations at airports.","false","Biography information for Baroness Randerson",,"Baroness Randerson","HL2381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775974","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-27","<p>The Department for Transport carries out regular assessments of aviation security at all last points of departure airports to the UK from Egypt. It is long standing government policy not to comment, or publish, details on security matters. However the Government works closely with international partners, including airlines, airports and the Egyptian Government, on security standards. The Government hopes to be in a position to change travel advice to enable flights to the UK from Sharm El Sheikh as soon as security conditions allow.</p>",,"Lord Callanan","HL2383","2017-10-27T10:40:33.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775974/answer","Biography information for Lord Callanan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775974/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775974/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-23","Aviation: Egypt","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what measurements of safety levels they apply to Sharm El Sheikh airport.","false","Biography information for Lord Risby",,"Lord Risby","HL2382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775975","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-27","<p>The Department for Transport carries out regular assessments of aviation security at all last points of departure airports to the UK from Egypt. It is long standing government policy not to comment, or publish, details on security matters. However the Government works closely with international partners, including airlines, airports and the Egyptian Government, on security standards. The Government hopes to be in a position to change travel advice to enable flights to the UK from Sharm El Sheikh as soon as security conditions allow.</p>",,"Lord Callanan","HL2382","2017-10-27T10:40:33.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775975/answer","Biography information for Lord Callanan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775975/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775975/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-23","Aviation: Egypt","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they will publish the report arising from the most recent inspection of Sharm El Sheikh airport.","false","Biography information for Lord Risby",,"Lord Risby","HL2383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775976","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>Despite Her Majesty's Government's ban on flights to Sharm El Sheikh, British tourists continue to visit Egypt. Our Travel Advice does not advise against travel to many parts of Egypt. So far this year, UK tourists have contributed over $153 million to the Egyptian economy. Britain is the number two western European country in terms of numbers of tourists in Egypt.</p><p>The Egyptian Tourism Minister stated in 2015 that flight suspensions following the Metrojet attack had resulted in direct losses estimated at $280 million a month to the Egyptian economy. This figure included the impact of flight suspensions by a number of countries. ​</p><p>We know the importance of tourism in Sharm El Sheikh and are in constant dialogue with the Egyptian government. Our Travel Advice can have trade and political implications, but we do not let this determine the advice we give. The safety of British nationals has to be our main concern.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2017-11-06T17:38:45.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775976/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775976/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775976/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-23","Egypt: Aviation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what estimate they have made of the loss to the Egyptian economy if the ban on Sharm El Sheikh continues within the World Tourism Market, to be held at Earls Court on 4 November.","false","Biography information for Lord Risby",,"Lord Risby","HL2384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775977","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-06","<p>We do not collect information on the economic value of outbound flights to specific global destinations and the value of them to the UK travel market. Therefore, it is difficult to make any assessment of the impact on the UK economy, since holidaymakers who would have booked to visit Sharm El Sheikh may have booked flights to other destinations instead. This would still benefit the UK travel industry.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde","HL2386","2017-11-06T12:22:43.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775977/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775977/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775977/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-23","Tourism: Egypt","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what estimate they have made of the loss to the UK travel industry if the ban on Sharm el Sheikh continues within the World Tourism Market, to be held at Earls Court on 4 November.","false","Biography information for Lord Risby",,"Lord Risby","HL2385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775978","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-06","<p>We do not collect information on the economic value of outbound flights to specific global destinations and the value of them to the UK travel market. Therefore, it is difficult to make any assessment of the impact on the UK economy, since holidaymakers who would have booked to visit Sharm El Sheikh may have booked flights to other destinations instead. This would still benefit the UK travel industry.</p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde","HL2385","2017-11-06T12:22:43.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775978/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775978/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775978/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-23","Tourism: Egypt","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what estimate they have made of the economic impact on the UK travel industry of the ban on direct flights between the UK and Sharm el Sheikh airport since the ban was imposed in 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord Risby",,"Lord Risby","HL2386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775979","Department of Health","false","2017-11-02","<p>There are no mechanisms in place for routine monitoring of the take-up of advice given on the NHS Choices website about preventing pregnancies affected by neural tube defects.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-11-02T14:46:48.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775979/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775979/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775979/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-23","Neural Tube Defects","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how the take-up of advice given on National Health Service websites about preventing pregnancies affected by neural tube defects is monitored.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL2387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775980","Department of Health","false","2017-11-01","<p>This data is not held centrally.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-11-01T12:56:03.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775980/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775980/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775980/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-23","Folic Acid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they have any recent measurements of the take-up of folic acid supplements by women of child-bearing age; and whether any such measurements show differences in trends between different age groups.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL2388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775981","Home Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>The file has now been reviewed and prepared for transfer to The National Archives. A date for this transfer is being arranged, and is expected to be in either December or January.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-11-06T17:16:21.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775981/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775981/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775981/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-23","Hilda Murrell","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Williams of Trafford on 17 July (HL641), what was the outcome of the review of the file relating to Hilda Murrell.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL2389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775982","Home Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>There is one Home Office file, ref. HO/287/3597/1, relating to Hilda Murrell which contains two extracts that are closed until 1 January 2070. This is because of the requirement to protect the personal data of living individuals under s40(2) of the Freedom of Information Act 2000.</p><p><a href="http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/r/C14589950" target="_blank">http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/r/C14589950</a></p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-11-06T17:15:27.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775982/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775982/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775982/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-23","Hilda Murrell","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government why there are files relating to Hilda Murrell in the Home Office or Public Record Office which are closed until 1 January 2070.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL2390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775983","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>Together with our international partners we are monitoring this case closely. We continue to raise our concerns about the persecution of members of the LGBT community in Chechnya with the Russian authorities at a senior level. Most recently the Minister for Europe and the Americas raised the persecution of members of the LGBT community in Chechnya with Senator Aleksey Pushkov on Wednesday 25 October.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2017-11-06T16:03:06.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775983/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775983/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775983/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-23","Zelimkhan Bakaev","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what representations they have made to the governments of (1) Russia, and (2) Chechnya, about reports that Zelimkhan Bakaev, a Russian singer, was arrested, tortured, and murdered by Chechen authorities due to suspicion of homosexuality.","false","Biography information for Lord Scriven",,"Lord Scriven","HL2391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775984","Home Office","false","2017-11-01","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford","HL2393 ; HL2395","2017-11-01T14:08:57.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775984/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775984/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/775984/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-23","Police: Biometrics","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many facial biometric recognition systems are being used by police forces in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Lord Scriven",,"Lord Scriven","HL2392"
