"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776028","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-26","<p>As of 25 October 2017, there were 229 UK military personnel stationed in the United Arab Emirates. This is broken down, by Service, below:</p><p>Royal Navy: 50</p><p>British Army: 37</p><p>Royal Air Force: 145</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-26T13:39:14.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776028/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776028/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776028/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-23","United Arab Emirates: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK personnel from each of the armed forces are stationed in the United Arab Emirates.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","109061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776029","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-26","<p>The construction dates for each of the Hawk TMk1 training aircraft in the Royal Air Force fleet are not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost, however the aircraft were manufactured between the mid-1970s and mid-1980s.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-26T15:04:12.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776029/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776029/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776029/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-23","Hawk Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the construction dates are of each of the Hawk TMk1 training aircraft in the Royal Air Force Fleet.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","108984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776030","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-26","<p>Information about the Red Arrows display income for financial years 2015-16 to 2017-18 is provided below. Information prior to 2015-16 is not readily available.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Amount £000</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>425</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>442</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>We do not hold information about income earned by charity organisations who have paid for displays or flypasts.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-26T15:02:37.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776030/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776030/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776030/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-23","Red Arrows","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much (a) accrued to the public purse and (b) was made for charity in paid-for displays and flypasts by the Red Arrows in (i) their recent tour of the Middle East and (ii) each fiscal year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","108985"
