"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776255","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-01","<p>As of 31 March 2017, the following percentages of land were designated as Green Belt in Bolton, Wigan and Greater Manchester:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Bolton</p></td><td><p>52</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wigan</p></td><td><p>57</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Greater Manchester</p></td><td><p>47</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-11-01T17:30:04.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776255/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776255/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776255/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-23","Green Belt: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of land in (a) Bolton, (b) Wigan and (c) Greater Manchester has been designated green belt land.","false","Biography information for Chris Green","Bolton West","Chris Green","109112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776256","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-26","<p>Figures on public sector spend at a regional and national level are part of the Government’s Country and Regional Analysis (CRA) statistics. These statistics attempt to allocate the spending according to where the benefits of that spend are accrued.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics for public capital expenditure on transport for the North West of England for the years 2014-15 and 2015-16 are given below:</p><p> </p><p>2014-15: £1.355 billion</p><p>2015-16: £1.853 billion</p><p> </p><p>These figures include spend on transport by all public sector organisations (including Local Authorities and Public Corporations).</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-10-26T15:01:50.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776256/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776256/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776256/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-23","Transport: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much the Government has allocated to transport capital infrastructure projects in the North West of England in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Chris Green","Bolton West","Chris Green","109103"
